item.description:
Often it is useful to save python data to json files. The following code will demonstrate how that can be done.
 &ldquo;God bless JSON!&rdquo; ~ a soon to be famous programmer
 import json data = {'a': 1, 'b':'hello', 'c':False} filename = 'awesome_data.json' # write data to file with open(filename, 'w') as f: json.dump(data, f) # read json from file with open(filename, 'r') as f: data = json.load(f) print(data) # prints {'a': 1, 'b':'hello', 'c':False}
